    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThere is an unexpected dash in the right most column of message area under certain conditions.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. `:set columns=12`\r\n3. Press `v`. This will result into `-1         -` being shown in the bottom line. This seems out of place because it shows `--1          ` with `columns=13`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither `--          ` or `-1          ` being shown in the bottom line.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1e7e9ee\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.5.5-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The root cause is that it tries to display both showcmd and showmode only when one could fit.\r\n\r\nin `-1` the - comes from showmode and 1 from showcmd, and the final result makes no sense.",
